<div class="page-body is-centered">

    <p>
        By day I'm a software engineer and architect. By night I'm building things nobody asked me to build, pulling espresso shots and wondering whether Minneapolis summers are actually getting hotter or if I'm just getting older.
    </p>

    <p>
        This blog is where I write about code, coffee, AI, side projects, and whatever else has my attention. Some posts are technical. Some are about weather data. Some are about buying a printer or starting a t-shirt company that didn't go anywhere. I try not to filter it too hard.
    </p>

    <p>
        I've been writing software for a long time and building things on the side for most of that. <a href="https://mncoffeemap.com">MN Coffee</a> is a map I made because I couldn't find a good one. <a href="https://todaysrecordhigh.com">Today's Record High</a> exists because I got curious about climate data and went too far with it. That's kind of how these things go.
    </p>

    <p>
        If something I wrote was useful to you, or you just want to say hi, the <a href="/contact">contact page</a> is right there. 
    </p>

</div>
